- Side effects occuring at **therapeutic range**: **Fine tremor**, *polyuria*, *polydypsia*, metallic taste, goiter, hypothyroidism, weight gain, oedema, *diabetes insipidus* and arrhythmias

[!INFO] Giardiasis is one of the most common intestinal infections worldwide in both developed and developing countries

  • Cyst is the infective stage. (Cysts are immediately infectious upon excretion, they can survive chlorinated water)
  • Cyst are ingested via contaminated water or food (like salads). Faeco-oral person to person transmission can occurs (eg. Child care centers)
  • Abdominal pain, watery diarrhea, weight loss.
  • can cause malabsorption in paediatric population.
  • Severe infection can invade the mucosa in severe infection but usually there is no invasion.
  • Can rarely invade pancreas and bile ducts.
  • Diagnosis : stool microscopy, string test, also PCR on stools samples.
  • Treatment: tinidazol, metronidazole is second line due to concern of side effects. Achieves parasite clearance within 1 week.

Arterial PO2 remains NORMAL!* ==> No stimulation of respiration despite low oxygen delivery to tissues -> pobably no respiratory alkalosis
But some sources say respiratory alkalosis can occur.
